Privacy Policy
Last updated: January 21, 2026
This Privacy Policy describes how Mathy (“we”, “our”, or “the app”) handles information when you use our mobile application designed for children.
We are committed to protecting children’s privacy and complying with applicable privacy laws, including the Children’s Online Privacy Protection Act (COPPA).
1. Information We Collect
1.1 Personal Information
We do not collect, store, or share any personal information from children or parents.
This includes (but is not limited to):
Name
Email address
Phone number
Location data
Photos or videos
1.2 Automatically Collected Information
Our app does not collect:
Device identifiers
Advertising IDs
IP addresses
Usage analytics tied to individuals
The app works offline and does not require user accounts.
2. Use of Artificial Intelligence (AI)
Mathy uses on-device AI to help children learn numbers by writing them.
All processing happens locally on the device.
No handwriting data is sent to any server
No data is stored or shared externally
3. Third-Party Services
We do not use third-party services that collect data from users, such as:
Analytics tools
Advertising networks
Social media SDKs
If this changes in the future, this Privacy Policy will be updated accordingly.
4. In-App Purchases / Subscriptions (If Applicable)
If the app offers paid features:
Payments are processed only by Google Play / App Store
We do not receive or store payment information
Parental approval is required according to platform rules
5. Children’s Privacy
This app is intended for children under the age of 13.
We do not knowingly collect personal data from children
No registration or login is required
Parents can safely allow children to use the app independently
6. Data Security
Since we do not collect or store personal data, there is no risk of personal data exposure from our systems.
7. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time.
Any changes will be posted on this page with an updated “Last updated” date.
8. Contact Us
If you have any questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy, you can contact us at:
Email: ohangor@gmail.com
Developer: Gor Ohanyan
